## Platform deployment (PaaS)

Supported providers: Railway, Render, Fly.io, Vercel, Netlify, DigitalOcean.

After `my deploy setup`, configuration files are written to the project root (e.g. `railway.json`, `fly.toml`).

## Terraform (IaaS)

For AWS, GCP, and Azure, Terraform lives under `deploy/terraform/<provider>/`:

```bash
cd deploy/terraform/<provider>
terraform init
terraform plan
terraform apply
```

AWS stacks are split into `main.tf`, `network.tf`, `database.tf`, and `storage.tf`.

See `TERRAFORM.md` and per-provider `deploy/terraform/*/TERRAFORM.md`.

## Secrets

Configure tokens per provider in `deploy/secrets.<provider>.md` (generated by `my deploy setup`).

Sync from `.env`:

```bash
my deploy secrets sync --provider <%= provider %> --dry-run
```

